Cross-Border Data Breach Investigation

Background
A multinational financial services company discovers that a former employee in Singapore has accessed confidential client data from servers located in the United States.
The employee, now residing in Malaysia, is suspected of selling customer information to competitors.
The company has identified the unauthorized access through logs but has not yet contacted law enforcement.

Key Details
•	Victim Organization: Fortune 500 financial services company
•	Location of Servers: United States (New York)
•	Suspect Location: Malaysia
•	Former Employee Status: Terminated 6 months ago
•	Data Compromised: Personal financial information of 50,000 clients
•	Evidence Available: Server logs, email communications, financial transactions
•	Company Concern: Potential regulatory fines under GDPR and other data protection laws
